  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Slice the<strong> chestnut mushrooms </strong>finely</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick), with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced mushrooms</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-mushroom-leek-and-gnocchi-gratin/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the mushrooms are cooking, wash the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice finely</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-mushroom-leek-and-gnocchi-gratin/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>leek</strong> to the pan with the mushrooms and reduce the heat to medium-low</p><p>Cook for 8-9 min further or until the leek has softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-mushroom-leek-and-gnocchi-gratin/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Combine the<strong> panko</strong> <strong>breadcrumbs</strong> with the <strong>dried</strong> <strong>basil</strong>, a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> pepper </strong>– this is your<strong> basil crumb</strong></p><p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[550ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and add the <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>soft cheese</strong> and a very generous grind of <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your<strong> stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-mushroom-leek-and-gnocchi-gratin/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>gnocchi</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-mushroom-leek-and-gnocchi-gratin/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has softened, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>to the pan and cook for 1 min, then gradually add the <strong>stock</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further or until a creamy consistency – this is your <strong>creamy mushroom mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-mushroom-leek-and-gnocchi-gratin/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top the <strong>gnocchi </strong>with the<strong> creamy mushroom mixture</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Top with the<strong> basil crumb</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until the basil crumb is golden and crispy – this is your <strong>mushroom, leek & gnocchi gratin</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-mushroom-leek-and-gnocchi-gratin/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Leave the <strong>mushroom, leek & gnocchi gratin</strong> to stand for 5 min before serving (this helps the flavours to develop and makes it easier to serve!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
